 need to know\n","* int(): this can only contain integer values\n","* float(): used to store decimal numbers\n","* str(): used to store strings (text)\n","\n","for example:\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"m50sgbIor8VK","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1626847924401,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":795,"user":{"displayName":"Vibhav Kharangate","photoUrl":"","userId":"06933710891066087952"}},"outputId":"ebe9db9a-baaf-43a0-899e-8da9523f0698"},"source":["x=str(10)\n","print(type(x))     #to check the datatype of any item we can use the type method\n","\n","x=int(10)\n","print(type(x)) \n","\n","x=float(10)\n","print(type(x)) "],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","text":["<class 'str'>\n","<class 'int'>\n","<class 'float'>\n"],"name":"stdout"}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"IM0uHnwGsXBJ"},"source":["##Input\n","\n","We might want to take certain data directly from the user and use it in our code. For that we have the input method.\n","\n","\n","\n","```\n","variable=input('question that you want to prompt to the user')\n","```\n","\n","Example\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"ExOR2r9Zswri","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1626848091600,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":4115,"user":{"displayName":"Vibhav Kharangate","photoUrl":"","userId":"06933710891066087952"}},"outputId":"a0eca4d9-87fa-4bc1-eaaa-242dc0ca2c6a"},"source":["name=input('Please enter your name ')\n","\n","print(name)"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","text":["Please enter your name batman\n","batman\n"],"name":"stdout"}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"w8t_aAdH6Bux"},"source":["note that input is always stored as string. As such, if we are inputing numbers with the intent of using it in arithmatic operations, then we should 1st convert them to int or float\n","\n","For example, \n","\n","lets print the age of the u